1) https://nodejs.org/en/download/
Install nodejs
2) Copy install location, follow the installation
C:\Program Files\nodejs\
3)Restart the system
4)Open command line
npm install -g react-native-cli
5) Navigate the directory where you want to create the first React native project
react-native init "WelcomeProject"
6) Navigate to "WelcomeProject"
npm install
react-native run android
7) In "WelcomeProject" go inside the Android project, and create local.properties file and add below line
sdk.dir="Your SDK path"
If you are feeling difficulty here copy this local.properties file from any other Android project and paste it here
8) You can skip the step 7 by, opening the Android project directly by Android Studio

